<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        MUD GUARDS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MUD GUARDS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Mud Guard - Removal</title>
            <para>Mud guards are attached to the lower fender extension assembly. The mud guards protect the lower cab
                and step area from stones and mud.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900321" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900321.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. 41/42/43/4400 Series Mud Guards</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEX BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. HEX NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. MUD GUARD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Reference
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900321">Figure 21</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lock washers and hex nuts (Items 5 and 6). Remove the mud guard reinforcement
                    (Items 4 and 7) and the mud guard.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hex head bolts and flat washers (Items 2 and 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the procedure to remove the opposite side mud guard and reinforcement.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Mud Guard - Install</title>
            <para>Beginning on the drivers side of the vehicle.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the mud guard and reinforcement on the lower section of the fender extension.
                    Insert the hex head bolt and flat washer through the fender extension, mud guard and reinforcement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lock washer and hex nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten to 125 to 145 lbf-in. (14 to 16 N.m).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
